-## Forbidden Recovery Shortcuts
+When checkbox-49 is retried, the supervisor should constrain the daemon to one of these narrow cycles.
 
-Do not create private DevHub session files, auth state, traces, screenshots, raw crawl output, downloaded documents, credentials, or live crawler output as part of supervisor repair. Do not mark PP&D domain tasks complete unless validation has accepted the implementation artifacts for that task.
+Cycle A: minimal contract skeleton
+
+- Edit only `ppd/contracts/public_source_inventory.py` and one focused test file.
+- Add or repair only the public validation entry point, finding data structure, host allowlist check, provenance-required-field check, and unsafe-field key detection.
+- Do not add live crawling, HTTP requests, downloaded documents, browser traces, screenshots, auth state, credentials, or raw response fixtures.
+- Require `python3 -m py_compile ppd/contracts/public_source_inventory.py` before unit tests.
+
+Cycle B: raw-body rejection fixture
+
+- Edit only the invalid inventory fixture and the matching assertion.
+- Ensure at least one invalid record contains a literal raw response body field such as `raw_response_body` or `response_body`.
+- Ensure the validator reports the exact reason `raw response body field is not allowed in public source inventories`.
+- Do not introduce multiline raw HTML bodies; use a short sentinel string such as `REDACTED_RAW_BODY_SENTINEL` so the fixture remains non-sensitive and deterministic.
+
+Cycle C: provenance completeness
+
+- Edit only the valid and invalid inventory fixtures plus the focused validation test.
+- Check required provenance fields only: source URL, canonical URL, captured or verified timestamp, authority label, and fixture provenance note.
+- Do not expand the validator into crawler policy, robots handling, archive adapters, or document extraction.
+
+## Syntax Guardrails
+
+For any retry after a Python SyntaxError:
+
+- Prefer one Python file plus one test file at most.
+- Avoid long generated helper functions.
+- Avoid nested f-strings, inline regex construction, or multiline string literals in generated code.
+- Keep rejection reasons as module-level string constants.
+- Run py_compile before the full PP&D validation command.
+
+For any retry after TypeScript TS1005, TS1109, or TS1128:
+
+- Prefer one TypeScript file at most.
+- Avoid broad type contract rewrites.
+- Run the TypeScript command before broader tests.
+
+## Task Selection Rule
+
+If a task is blocked and the active task does not depend on the blocked task, the daemon may continue with the active task. For the current state, checkbox-51 may continue because it validates the normalized document link graph and should not require the unfinished public source inventory validator.
+
+If a task depends on checkbox-49, insert a narrow prerequisite task instead of attempting live crawl or authenticated automation.
+
+Suggested prerequisite task text:
+
+- [ ] Add a syntax-first public source inventory validator skeleton that emits deterministic finding reasons for allowlist, private DevHub path, unsafe artifact field, raw body field, credential field, and missing provenance checks using only committed fixtures.
+
+## Forbidden Recovery Paths
+
+The supervisor must not ask the daemon to recover checkbox-49 by creating or committing any of the following:
+
+- Private DevHub session files.
+- Auth state.
+- Credentials.
+- Browser traces.
+- Screenshots.
+- Raw crawl output.
+- Downloaded public or private documents.
+- Live DevHub automation.
+- CAPTCHA, MFA, account creation, payment, submission, certification, cancellation, official upload, or inspection scheduling automation.
+
+## Acceptance Criteria For Unblocking Checkbox-49
+
+Checkbox-49 may be considered unblocked only when all are true:
+
+- The validator module compiles with py_compile.
+- Unit tests cover one valid inventory and one invalid inventory.
+- Invalid inventory findings include all required reason categories.
+- The raw response body rejection reason is emitted by an actual fixture field, not only by test-side expectation.
+- No committed fixture contains raw response bodies, credentials, trace paths, screenshot paths, downloaded document paths, private DevHub paths, or live crawl artifacts except short redacted sentinel strings used only to prove rejection.
